docs.abstract: Bolstered by newfound economic strength, European leaders, steered by the French president, Emmanuel Macron, are pledging to further integrate the continent.
docs.snippet: Bolstered by newfound economic strength, European leaders, steered by the French president, Emmanuel Macron, are pledging to further integrate the continent.
docs.lead_paragraph: DAVOS, Switzerland — French President Emmanuel Macron laid claim to the mantle of leader of the free world on Wednesday, with an ambitious speech before a packed assembly at the World Economic Forum.

headline.main: Europe Is Back. And Rejecting Trumpism.
headline.print_headline: Flexing New Economic Strength, European Leaders Issue a Rebuttal to Trump

docs.abstract: By alienating allies, the United States could undermine the potential for collective action among countries nursing shared grievances with China.
docs.snippet: By alienating allies, the United States could undermine the potential for collective action among countries nursing shared grievances with China.
docs.lead_paragraph: LONDON — In recent history as narrated by President Trump, the United States has been fleeced and humiliated by savvier nations unrestrained by naïve notions like global trading rules. Predatory powers have exploited American weakness to steal factory jobs, sowing despair.

headline.main: Trump Says Getting Tough on Chinese Trade Will Empower the U.S. He Risks the Opposite.
headline.print_headline: In Getting Tough on Chinese Trade, Trump Risks Alienating Allies

docs.abstract: When the company bought the elegant Waldorf Astoria, few had heard of it — but its founder and many board members made the most of impressive connections.
docs.snippet: When the company bought the elegant Waldorf Astoria, few had heard of it — but its founder and many board members made the most of impressive connections.
docs.lead_paragraph: HONG KONG — Anbang Insurance Group burst onto the global deal-making scene in 2014 when it announced a nearly $2 billion deal to purchase the Waldorf Astoria hotel, an Art Deco symbol of New York’s Champagne-soaked upper-crust life.

headline.main: What Is Anbang? A Primer on China’s Fallen Deal Maker

docs.abstract: The electric-car maker said output of its first mass-market offering, the Model 3, was up to 2,000 a week. But that’s still short of the goal set by Elon Musk.
docs.snippet: The electric-car maker said output of its first mass-market offering, the Model 3, was up to 2,000 a week. But that’s still short of the goal set by Elon Musk.
docs.lead_paragraph: Tesla began producing electric cars at its plant in Fremont, Calif., six years ago, starting with small quantities and ramping up to about 100,000 vehicles last year. Now, as it tries to double or triple that number, the company and its chief executive, Elon Musk, are getting a lesson in how hard it is to mass-produce automobiles.

headline.main: For Tesla, ‘Production Hell’ Looks Like the Reality of the Car Business
headline.print_headline: Output Goals At Tesla Meet Cold Reality Of Industry

docs.abstract: Production delays, a recall and other problems have presented the electric-car maker and its founder, Elon Musk, with a crisis of confidence among investors.
docs.snippet: Production delays, a recall and other problems have presented the electric-car maker and its founder, Elon Musk, with a crisis of confidence among investors.
docs.lead_paragraph: Just a year ago, Tesla looked like a rising force destined to revolutionize the auto industry.

headline.main: Tesla Looked Like the Future. Now Some Ask if It Has One.
headline.print_headline: Tesla in Need Of Recharge After a Series Of Setbacks

docs.abstract: Days after a news report focused on conditions at the plant, a California agency said it was investigating an episode that left a millwright’s jaw broken.
docs.snippet: Days after a news report focused on conditions at the plant, a California agency said it was investigating an episode that left a millwright’s jaw broken.
docs.lead_paragraph: Tesla is already under scrutiny because of its uncertain financial outlook, troubles producing a new model and safety questions about its driver-assistance technology.

headline.main: Tesla Factory Safety Under Scrutiny After Worker Is Injured
headline.print_headline: California Scrutinizes Tesla Plant After Injury

docs.abstract: Eight months into its chief’s tenure, the company’s stock is languishing and some analysts are perplexed. Disappointing earnings added to the puzzle.
docs.snippet: Eight months into its chief’s tenure, the company’s stock is languishing and some analysts are perplexed. Disappointing earnings added to the puzzle.
docs.lead_paragraph: Eight months after taking over as chief executive of Ford Motor, Jim Hackett is still trying to accomplish one of his most important tasks: convincing Wall Street that he has a compelling plan to reinvigorate the automaker.

headline.main: Ford Says It’s a New Era. Wall Street Isn’t Buying It.
headline.print_headline: New Chief Is Remaking Ford, but Is Gaining Little Traction With Investors

docs.abstract: Mark Begor will take over the credit reporting company, which is struggling to rebuild after a devastating data breach.
docs.snippet: Mark Begor will take over the credit reporting company, which is struggling to rebuild after a devastating data breach.
docs.lead_paragraph: Equifax on Wednesday named Mark Begor, a private equity executive who once led General Electric’s credit card business, as its new chief executive.

headline.main: Equifax Picks Private Equity Executive as New C.E.O.
headline.print_headline: Private Equity Executive Chosen to Lead Equifax

docs.abstract: Mick Mulvaney, the head of the Consumer Financial Protection Bureau, will move the student loan division into another unit, a shift officials fear will sidetrack cases against lenders.
docs.snippet: Mick Mulvaney, the head of the Consumer Financial Protection Bureau, will move the student loan division into another unit, a shift officials fear will sidetrack cases against lenders.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Mick Mulvaney, the interim director of the Consumer Financial Protection Bureau, will move the agency’s student loan division into the bureau’s consumer information unit, a shift that career officials fear will sidetrack a major enforcement case the agency is pursuing against Navient, the nation’s largest student loan collector.

headline.main: Mulvaney Downgrades Student Loan Unit in Consumer Bureau Reshuffle
headline.print_headline: Mulvaney Demotes Student Loan Unit in Consumer Bureau Reshuffle

byline.original: By Glenn Thrush and Stacy Cowley

docs.abstract: After a scandal involving fraudulent accounts, the central bank restricted the growth of Wells Fargo, which said it would replace four board members.
docs.snippet: After a scandal involving fraudulent accounts, the central bank restricted the growth of Wells Fargo, which said it would replace four board members.
docs.lead_paragraph: The Federal Reserve on Friday imposed unusually harsh penalties on Wells Fargo, punishing it for years of misconduct and barring it from future growth until the bank fixes its problems.

headline.main: Federal Reserve Shackles Wells Fargo After Fraud Scandal
headline.print_headline: Fed Shackles Wells Fargo Growth  With Severe Penalties for Abuses

byline.original: By Emily Flitter, Binyamin Appelbaum and Stacy Cowley
